{
  "texts": [
    "The text perplexity is considered low if the model can predict the subsequent word easily.",
    "On the other hand, vice versa, if the model finds the next word is difficult to predict, the text perplexity is ranked high.",
    "In other words, LLMs like ChatGPT are trained to produce text with low perplexity.",
    "However, it can mean that if human writers show limited word choices and use a lot of common words, the detector system can misjudge the text as AI-generated.",
    "The risk is much greater with non-native English speakers because they are more prone to use simple words than native English speakers."
  ]
}